potion-base-8M — vendored static embedding model
=================================================

Source:  https://huggingface.co/minishlab/potion-base-8M
Author:  MinishLab (Model2Vec)
License: MIT

A Model2Vec static embedding model, distilled from the BAAI/bge-base-en-v1.5
Sentence Transformer. Static token embeddings (no transformer forward pass):
a text is embedded by mean-pooling its token vectors and L2-normalizing.

Vendored here as:
  - potion-base-8m.pem.br            int8 per-row-quantized embedding matrix,
                                     brotli-compressed. Format (little-endian):
                                       magic "PEM1", u32 vocab, u32 dim,
                                       f32[vocab] row scales, i8[vocab*dim] weights.
                                     Dequantized to f32 at load (scale * weight).
                                     int8 quantization is retrieval-lossless here
                                     (vectors are re-normalized after pooling).
  - potion-base-8m.tokenizer.json.br the aligned HF tokenizer, brotli-compressed.

